This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the human visual perception system, which is closely related to the field of computer vision. The paper also mentions multi-task auxiliary learning, which is a common technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of subjective attention and task intention also suggests a potential overlap with human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the experimental verification of the proposed theory may involve the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
